reviews.review_text:
Hey! Hey! Absolute scorcher of a show. 

Great Good Times Roll into some sloppy performances of Stranger and Row Jimmy. Timing issues here and there, but the first set has great energy. Jerry belts out a killer Ramble on Rose. Then comes Let it Grow. Easily the best performance I have heard in the late-80s. The beginning of the jam will stand your hair on end. The band just absolutely crushes it. 

The second set is great from end to end. China>Rider>Saturday Night encore? All awesome.
